<div id="review_3424658692" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3424658692" />
    <a title="Janelle" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/88713906-janelle"><img alt="Janelle" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1581393896p2/88713906.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3424658692?book_show_action=true">Jul 05, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Janelle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Janelle" href="/user/show/88713906-janelle">Janelle</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/88713906-janelle?shelf=2020">2020</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/88713906-janelle?shelf=library">library</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3424658692" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18302793477342838763">It’s about time I read this as J.G.Ballard is one of my favourite writers(I have seen the film though)! It is a fictionalised account of his experiences in Shanghai as a boy during WWII. it is a story of survival and resilience in harsh conditions and being exposed to many things that would be hard for most people to cope with.<br/>It’s written in a stark and a matter of fact way but is difficult to put down. The character of Jim is intelligent, and somehow hopeful, he makes himself useful to survive</span>
  <span id="freeText18302793477342838763" style="display:none">It’s about time I read this as J.G.Ballard is one of my favourite writers(I have seen the film though)! It is a fictionalised account of his experiences in Shanghai as a boy during WWII. it is a story of survival and resilience in harsh conditions and being exposed to many things that would be hard for most people to cope with.<br />It’s written in a stark and a matter of fact way but is difficult to put down. The character of Jim is intelligent, and somehow hopeful, he makes himself useful to survive.<br />Already we can see some of Ballard’s later obsessions coming through. Empty buildings particularly old military facilities, wreckage of planes, empty houses and the atom bomb, isolation and loneliness, even when in a group and the things people do when normal life has been upturned.<br />A thought provoking read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18302793477342838763" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


